cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is about text matching using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which could place it under cs.IR and cs.AI, respectively. Finally, the paper uses contextual features, which could suggest a connection to computer vision (CV) and image processing, making cs.CV a possible sub-category as well.
